libcsocks5 - simple SOCKS 5 client library

for now, only IPv4 and domain-name are tested.


API
---
- Create context
struct socks_ctx *socks_init(void);

- Set authentication (RFC1929 only)
int socks_set_auth(struct socks_ctx *, const char *, const char *);

- Set SOCKS server
int socks_set_server(struct socks_ctx *, const char *, const char *);

- Connect to the SOCKS server
int socks_connect_server(struct socks_ctx *);

- Set IPv4 address and port destination (TESTED and WORKED)
int socks_set_addr4(struct socks_ctx *, const char *, const char *);

- Set IPv6 address and port to destination (NOT TESTED YET)
int socks_set_addr6(struct socks_ctx *, const char *, const char *);

- Set Fully qualified domain name and port to connect (TESTED and WORKED)
int socks_set_addrname(struct socks_ctx *, const char *, const char *);

- Perform a SOCKS request
int socks_connect(struct socks_ctx *);

If socks_connect() success, it returns a file descriptor that you can use
just like a simple socket() + connect() socket, you can use socket operations
like send(), write(), recv(), read(), etc...

- All done
void socks_end(struct socks_ctx *);


references
----------
- [RFC1928]  SOCKS Protocol Version 5
- [RFC1929]  Username/Password Authentication for SOCKS V5
